43045-item-14543071\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 5 days, 18 hours ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/hozayx/\" title=\"View hozayx&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">hozayx</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/b7rqnbOvogE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hozayx\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/_-is-not-defined-and-a-bunch-of-500-protocol-errors/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:180:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Access-control-allow-origin header contains multiple values\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/9c1hMqeUY4g/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 06:30:28 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/access-control-allow-origin-header-contains-multiple-values/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1538:\"<p>Replies: 5</p>\n						<p>Hi,<br />\nUsing W3 Total Cache and Cloudways CDN refuses to load any of the fonts and gives the following message:</p>\n<p><code>Access to font at &#039;https://118456-337960-4-raikfcquaxqncofqfm.stackpathdns.com/wp-content/themes/pixxy-child-theme/assets/fonts/Satisfy-Regular.ttf&#039; from origin &#039;https://staging.fletcherssolicitors.co.uk&#039; has been blocked by CORS policy: The &#039;Access-Control-Allow-Origin&#039; header contains multiple values &#039;*, *&#039;, but only one is allowed.</code></p>\n<p>In the CDN settings I have removed the fonts from the list in the &#8220;Theme File Types&#8221; field, which now only contains:  *.css;*.js;*.gif;*.png;*.jpg;*.ico;*.less</p>\n<p>The fonts are still being served from the CDN and therefore will always be blocked by the browser due to the CORS header duplication.  I am at a loss with this &#8211; none of the fonts will load at all when served from the CDN and I cannot STOP them from being uploaded to the CDN, W3TC just ignores the fact that there are no fonts in the Theme File Types field.  </p>\n<p>Is this a bug?  How can fonts still be included in the CDN when they aren&#8217;t being specified as a file type?</p>\n<p>Ideally I would like to host the fonts on the CDN but CORS won&#8217;t allow me, and so now I would like to host everything but the fonts on the CDN, but W3TC keeps uploading them!  Vicious circle.</p>\n<p>Any ideas?</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/9c1hMqeUY4g\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"antforshaw\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/access-control-allow-origin-header-contains-multiple-values/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:15;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:183:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;error 502 and redirect to home page with w3 total cache plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/fFCBj9wWOg8/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 06:23:49 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/error-502-and-redirect-to-home-page-with-w3-total-cache-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:294:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>unable to open wp-admin<br />\ni get random 502 errors.<br />\nrunning on ngix server. with php 7.2 running on server. </p>\n<p>how to complete get rid of your plugin?</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/fFCBj9wWOg8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"aashishbhargav\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/error-502-and-redirect-to-home-page-with-w3-total-cache-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:16;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:143:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Page cache not cleared\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/QfysG7UjkNU/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 03:34:15 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/page-cache-not-cleared/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1212:\"<p>Replies: 5</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>we use this theme <a href=\"https://themeforest.net/item/mylisting-directory-listing-wordpress-theme/20593226\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://themeforest.net/item/mylisting-directory-listing-wordpress-theme/20593226</a> (quite famous and used a LOT). However, we have some regular pages like here <a href=\"https://www.spots4kite.com/croatia/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://www.spots4kite.com/croatia/</a> and when we add a new listing then the cache is not purged and this page and also homepage is not purged and updated. </p>\n<p>This is the answer to our question by the author:</p>\n<p><em>Listings are posts that belong to a custom post type<br />\nI’m not familiar with the plugin but I assume it should have an option for custom post types as almost every premium theme out there uses custom post types one way or another unless it’s a simple blog theme.</p>\n<p>If you don’t find an option for custom post types, I would check with plugin author</em></p>\n<p>How can we set it up correctly to have the page cache cleared when a new listing is added?</p>\n<p>Thank you.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/QfysG7UjkNU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"keengamer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/page-cache-not-cleared/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:17;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Changes not showing on Chrome\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/dPw4ZcWNI9c/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 02:45:20 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/changes-not-showing-on-chrome/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1062:\"<p>Replies: 11</p>\n						<p>Hi. On my site, users are able to select their preferred gaming platform (PlayStation 4 / Xbox One) which will set a cookie. After loading a post, that cookie is read and the page will show that platform&#8217;s buttons.</p>\n<p><strong>The Problem:</strong> This works perfectly fine on Firefox. However on Chrome, when I change platforms and visit the page again, it will show the previous platform&#8217;s buttons instead of the newly selected one.</p>\n<p>I am wondering why this happens. What would I need to do to get this to work how I want it to? It would be great if the user&#8217;s cache is updated whenever they change the platform.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to try it yourself, you can do so by visiting my <a href=\"https://www.kombatakademy.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">site</a>, clicking on &#8220;Select Platform&#8221; at the top and clicking on one of the blog posts.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance!</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/dPw4ZcWNI9c\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"redraptor10\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/changes-not-showing-on-chrome/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:18;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:154:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;plugin caused my website to crash\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/_dZmTTPYZfk/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 01:34:41 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/plugin-caused-my-website-to-crash/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1165:\"<p>Replies: 7</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>Yesterday, it was an important day for one of my customer&#8217;s websites, as she launched a new series of products for summer, expecting many visitors from all around the globe. While she was updating / publishing products, she was purging all caches after a couple of actions, and suddenly the whole website crashed with an internal server error. She wasn&#8217;t able to login as an admin. We checked the resources usage and all the logs at that time, and it wasn&#8217;t a problem by the side of the server, everything was normal. We noticed that something was affecting the htaccess file, re-writing it all the time. We managed to delete and upload a new one, we then connected to the dashboard of the site and deleted the plugin (W3 Total Cache) and everything was fixed. Please, let me know what happened, it was a very very serious issue and we would like to avoid same situations in the future. Otherwise, I&#8217;m afraid we&#8217;ll find another way to add caching to our website.</p>\n<p>Thank you in advance,</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/_dZmTTPYZfk\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"dino123456789\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/plugin-caused-my-website-to-crash/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:19;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:135:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Paypal problem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/PGjKTAGNErI/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 00:29:13 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/paypal-problem-10/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:495:\"<p>Replies: 7</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I have a conflict problem with Paypal checkout.</p>\n<p>Buttons don&#8217;t work in cache after a while.</p>\n<p>How can I bypass this problem?</p>\n<p>button paypal: <a href=\"https://ibb.co/txcDy4F\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/txcDy4F</a><br />\nError: <a href=\"https://ibb.co/xhtFc8F\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/xhtFc8F</a></p>\n<p>Thank you</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/PGjKTAGNErI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lupus89\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/paypal-problem-10/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:20;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:162:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Global Caching issues with W3 Total Cache\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/Z8YR6ovoPao/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 09 Jun 2021 21:25:17 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/global-caching-issues-with-w3-total-cache/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1275:\"<p>Replies: 3</p>\n						<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve developed some issues with W3 Total Cache that appear to go away when I disable the plugin.</p>\n<p>For starters if the plugin is deactivated, clicking &#8216;activate&#8217; doesn&#8217;t activate it, or at least the plugin page doesn&#8217;t show that it is active and &#8216;Performance&#8217; does not appear in the top or side menu.</p>\n<p>I have to rename my W3 Total Cache folder via FTP, and then name it back again, for it to activate.</p>\n<p>When activated, nothing saves on my website and any changes I make either front end or back do not appear. For example, replying to a topic in bbpress either returns the &#8216;error &#8211; are you sure you want to do that?&#8217; message, or my reply isn&#8217;t displayed, even though it is recorded. When I disable W3 Total Cache, everything appears.</p>\n<p>Other development work in functions.php, for example, is not reflected either.</p>\n<p>This happens in all browsers, in Incognito mode, all browser cache deleted, all CDN cache purged. I have no other caching plugins running and there is no caching happening on my server. </p>\n<p>Any advice, please? Thank you.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/Z8YR6ovoPao\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"demonboy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/global-caching-issues-with-w3-total-cache/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:160:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Uploaded images into Azure Blob Storage\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/eaW0LWB5iM4/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 09 Jun 2021 07:11:09 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/uploaded-images-into-azure-blob-storage/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1199:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I purchased a license of your plugin but I have two questions:</p>\n<p>1. The first time I enter the website&#8217;s homepage the images are loaded without problem [1], then when I navigate to another page the images no longer appear [2]. If I refresh this new page the images reappear. It looks like it&#8217;s an error related to the image&#8217;s src [3], since the data-src is correct. As can be seen from the images below.</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://ibb.co/sVwn8y8\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/sVwn8y8</a><br />\n[2] <a href=\"https://ibb.co/f1VR3wM\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/f1VR3wM</a><br />\n[3] <a href=\"https://ibb.co/SVLxYjj\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/SVLxYjj</a></p>\n<p>2. I am using Azure Blob Storage to store images, and I would like to know if it would be possible to automate the process of uploading an image to Azure Blob Storage. I.e., whenever an image is ulploaded, it goes directly to Azure Blob Storage without me having to manually put it there, so that later when it is read there is no problem.</p>\n<p>Thanks</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/eaW0LWB5iM4\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"marioteixeira\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.o